1. classify each term as either:

A notatable symbol (flat, staccato, trill, barline, etc.)

A concept that maps to a notatable behavior (syncopation, cadence delay, motif, interval, etc.)

A concept that has no symbol and must be expressed with layout, text, or structure (genre rules, arrangement map, EDM build-drop, etc.)

2. convert every concept into one of four notation outputs:

glyph

marking

pattern

layout rule

3. build lessons that teach the player how to notate THAT category.

